                      <td valign="top" bgcolor="#ffffff"><b>Interruptions of BGP Sessions of Some Participants on 4 Apr 2011</b><br>
                        <br>
HKIX encountered intermittent MAC address table learning issues on Apr 4 2011 causing a couple of interruptions of BGP sessions of some HKIX participants.  The incidents were found caused by a local loop GE circuit from one HKIX participant and after detached the suspected connection from our network at 21:49pm HKT (GMT+8); HKIX services resumed normal.<br>
<br>
HKIX support team will keep monitoring the status and request the participant to check the local loop circuit with its circuit provider.</td>
